WEBVTT

00:05.806 --> 00:08.242
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:08.275 --> 00:10.777
Nancy: YES,
I SET THE HOUSE ON FIRE.

00:10.811 --> 00:11.812
WE'RE GOING TO REN MAR.

00:11.845 --> 00:12.946
HO, WHAT?!

00:12.980 --> 00:14.181
WE'RE GOING TO SEE BUBBIE.

00:14.214 --> 00:15.782
Shane:
WHAT'S SHE LIKE?

00:15.816 --> 00:17.451
SHE'S SOMEWHERE FAR,
FAR AWAY.

00:17.484 --> 00:20.420
IT'S A SHAME YOU BOYS
NEVER GOT A CHANCE TO KNOW HER.

00:20.454 --> 00:22.623
BUT YOU CAN BLAME
YOUR MOTHER FOR THAT.

00:22.656 --> 00:24.625
YEAH, YOU'RE NOT GETTING
OUT OF HERE ANYTIME SOON.

00:24.658 --> 00:27.261
YOU FUCKERS RATTED ME OUT.

00:27.294 --> 00:29.730
SHE GOT BUSTED
FOR A POT HOUSE.

00:29.763 --> 00:31.532
Your pot house, mom.
FUCK!

00:31.565 --> 00:33.166
SHOULD I BE NERVOUS
ABOUT ALL THIS?

00:33.200 --> 00:34.535
OF COURSE YOU SHOULD.

00:34.568 --> 00:37.004
IT'S THE DRUG BUSINESS.
IT'S DANGEROUS.

00:37.037 --> 00:39.706
YOU'RE GONNA TAKE A LITTLE DRIVE
FOR ME TODAY, BLANCA.

00:39.740 --> 00:42.242
AND THERE'S BIG MONEY IN IT
IF YOU DO IT REAL GOOD.

00:42.276 --> 00:43.477
WAIT, YOU WERE RECORDING ME,
AND THERE'S NO DRUGS?

00:43.510 --> 00:45.145
THE CAR WAS CLEAN?

00:45.179 --> 00:46.947
TOMORROW
WE REVIEW THE TAPE.

00:46.980 --> 00:48.715
NANCY, WHAT THE HELL
ARE WE DOING HERE?

00:48.749 --> 00:49.816
WE'RE STARTING A NEW LIFE.

00:49.850 --> 00:50.984
SHE'S TRYING TO TALK!

00:51.018 --> 00:52.986
Lenny:
IT'S YIDDISH.

00:53.020 --> 00:54.121
WHAT DID SHE SAY?

00:54.154 --> 00:55.989
IT MEANS "KILL ME."

00:59.993 --> 01:03.197
[ MONITOR BEEPING, AIR HISSING ]

01:10.838 --> 01:12.606
HER EYES DON'T MOVE,

01:12.639 --> 01:16.410
BUT THEY FOLLOW YOU LIKE
WHEN YOU LOOK AT A PAINTING.

01:16.443 --> 01:17.211
SHE'S LIKE A PAINTING.

01:17.244 --> 01:19.880
"SHE'S ALONE
AND PALELY LOITERING."

01:19.913 --> 01:22.916
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

01:22.950 --> 01:25.853
[ SIGHS ]

01:25.886 --> 01:27.621
HOW IS SHE?

01:27.654 --> 01:29.823
ALONE AND PALELY LOITERING.

01:29.857 --> 01:30.958
NICE COAT.

01:30.991 --> 01:34.094
KEPT ME TOASTY ON THE PORCH
LAST NIGHT.

01:34.127 --> 01:36.096
BUBBIE LOVES HER PELTS.

01:36.129 --> 01:37.865
WHAT WAS WRONG
WITH THE COUCH IN HERE?

01:37.898 --> 01:38.932
I GOT A LITTLE CREEPED OUT

01:38.966 --> 01:40.934
AFTER THE WHOLE
"I WANT TO DIE" THING.

01:40.968 --> 01:42.903
PLUS, IT'S LIKE BUNKING
WITH DARTH VADER.

01:42.936 --> 01:43.871
[ WHEEZING ]

01:43.904 --> 01:46.640
THE WHAT THING?

01:46.673 --> 01:49.409
YESTERDAY, BUBBIE TOLD US
SHE WANTS TO DIE.

01:49.443 --> 01:50.844
ACTUALLY, SHE SAID,
"KILL ME."

01:50.878 --> 01:52.145
IN YIDDISH.

01:52.179 --> 01:55.415
BUBBIE, THIS BUBBIE,
THE BUBBIE THAT DOESN'T BLINK?

01:55.449 --> 01:56.783
SHE SEIZED A MOMENT.

01:56.817 --> 01:58.352
IT WAS VERY INTENSE.

01:58.385 --> 02:01.722
SO SHE'S ACTUALLY IN THERE.
YEAH.

02:01.755 --> 02:02.956
AND SHE WANTS OUT.

02:02.990 --> 02:06.593
Lenny: I'VE GOT MANY LONG,
DARK HAIRS IN MY TUB!

02:06.627 --> 02:08.896
I'VE ACTUALLY GOT ONE
WRAPPED AROUND MY TOE!

02:08.929 --> 02:10.764
I'M THINKING, "DISGUSTING!"

02:10.797 --> 02:13.600
I'M ALSO THINKING
YOU'RE GOING BALD!

02:13.634 --> 02:14.768
DO WOMEN GO BALD?

02:14.801 --> 02:15.802
WHERE DID YOU COME FROM?

02:15.836 --> 02:17.104
OUTDOOR SHOWER.

02:17.137 --> 02:19.806
NO LINE. NO LENNY.

02:19.840 --> 02:22.242
WHERE THE HELL
IS MY BATHROBE?!

02:22.276 --> 02:25.979
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

02:31.718 --> 02:34.221
I BELIEVE
THIS BELONGS TO YOU.

02:35.789 --> 02:37.891
AND THAT BELONGS TO <i>ME.</i>

02:37.925 --> 02:39.927
ANOTHER THIEF.

02:39.960 --> 02:42.629
GOOD MORNING, SHANE.

02:42.663 --> 02:45.899
YOU, I'M NOT TALKING TO.

02:45.933 --> 02:48.368
IS THIS STILL
ABOUT ME BEING A THIEF?

02:48.402 --> 02:52.773
OR HAVE WE MOVED ON TO BUBBIE'S
RECENT TRIP TO CLARITYVILLE?

02:52.806 --> 02:54.441
"KILL ME."

02:54.474 --> 02:55.309
"KILL ME," HUH.

02:55.342 --> 02:57.611
WHAT DO YOU THINK
SHE MEANT BY THAT?

02:57.644 --> 03:01.215
MAYBE IT WAS HER SLED.

03:01.248 --> 03:03.784
I SAID I DIDN'T WANT TO
TALK TO YOU.

03:03.817 --> 03:05.252
BUT YOU DON'T LISTEN.

03:05.285 --> 03:07.521
YOU JUST KEEP ON TALKING,
DON'T YOU?!

03:07.554 --> 03:10.157
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]

03:10.190 --> 03:11.558
WOW.

03:11.592 --> 03:13.927
IT'S A LOT OF HAIR.

03:13.961 --> 03:17.564
YOU'RE UNDER A LOT
OF STRESS.

03:19.766 --> 03:23.904
WHAT DO YOU THINK BRINGS
TWO PEOPLE TOGETHER, MISS HODES,

03:23.937 --> 03:26.907
CHANCE OR FATE?

03:26.940 --> 03:29.176
CHANCE?

03:29.943 --> 03:32.145
NO, FATE.
IT'S F‐‐ IT'S FATE.

03:32.179 --> 03:33.947
IT'S DEFINITELY...FATE.

03:33.981 --> 03:35.182
WRONG.

03:36.850 --> 03:38.952
PLEASE DON'T PUT ME
BACK IN JAIL.

03:38.986 --> 03:39.987
IT'S CHANCE!

03:40.020 --> 03:42.055
AND I'M GONNA GIVE YOU ONE.

03:42.089 --> 03:44.591
A ONCE‐IN‐A‐LIFETIME,
NEVER‐TO‐BE‐REPEATED,

03:44.625 --> 03:49.196
SMALL‐WINDOW‐OF‐OPPORTUNITY
CHANCE TO CLEAR YOUR NAME.

03:49.229 --> 03:51.532
DOES THAT INTEREST YOU,
MISS HODES?

03:51.565 --> 03:53.367
YES, IT DOES. YES.

03:53.400 --> 03:55.903
I WANT TO KNOW
WHERE NANCY BOTWIN IS.

03:55.936 --> 03:58.172
I CAN DO THAT.

03:58.205 --> 04:01.842
I WANT TO KNOW HOW
SHE KNOWS THIS MAN,

04:01.875 --> 04:04.778
WHAT SHE'S DOING WITH HIM,
WHEN THEY MET,

04:04.811 --> 04:06.346
AND WHO INTRODUCED THEM.

04:06.380 --> 04:10.784
IF YOU CAN GIVE ME THE "WHY,"
I'LL SHIT SUNFLOWERS.

04:10.817 --> 04:13.587
AND THEN YOU'LL DROP
ALL THE CHARGES.

04:13.620 --> 04:15.889
DID I SAY THAT?

04:15.923 --> 04:16.890
NO.

04:16.924 --> 04:18.825
I DID NOT SAY THAT.

04:18.859 --> 04:22.129
I ALSO DID NOT NOT SAY THAT.

04:22.162 --> 04:26.500
WHAT YOU DELIVER TO ME,
I GIVE BACK TO YOU.

04:26.533 --> 04:31.205
QUALITY OF INFORMATION
EQUALS DEGREE OF LENIENCY.

04:31.238 --> 04:35.676
SO I‐I JUST, UH...WHAT?
KNOCK ON HER DOOR?

04:35.709 --> 04:40.814
SAY, "HEY, NANCE,
GOT ANY NEW MEXICAN FRIENDS?"

04:40.848 --> 04:42.382
ACTUALLY, HE'S PUERTO RICAN.

04:42.416 --> 04:45.252
HOW HE ENDED UP RUNNING
LOS ANGELES FOR A MEXICAN CARTEL

04:45.285 --> 04:47.087
IS SOMETHING
OF A MYSTERY TO US.

04:47.120 --> 04:50.624
GUILLERMO GARCIA‐GOMEZ.

04:50.657 --> 04:52.893
THAT'S WHO YOU WANT.

04:52.926 --> 04:54.828
OH, I'D LOVE HER, TOO.

04:54.862 --> 04:55.963
LOVE IT!

04:55.996 --> 04:58.799
BUT HER TIME'S COMING,
'CAUSE THAT'S FATE.

04:58.832 --> 05:00.934
BUT THIS GUY,
HE'S A WHALE.

05:00.968 --> 05:02.736
AND I FUCKING LOVE WHALES!

05:02.769 --> 05:06.840
I'M AHAB, MISS HODES.

05:06.874 --> 05:11.812
GUILLERMO GARCIA‐GOMEZ.

05:11.845 --> 05:14.715
YOU REPORT TO ME WEEKLY.

05:14.748 --> 05:17.718
AND, CELIA?

05:17.751 --> 05:19.119
YES?

05:20.554 --> 05:24.024
I LIKED YOU BLONDE
ON YOUR DRIVER'S LICENSE.

05:24.057 --> 05:27.761
THINK ABOUT
GOING THERE AGAIN.

05:32.332 --> 05:33.267
[ KEY CLICKS ]

05:33.300 --> 05:36.069
DO YOU HAVE ANYTHING
TO SAY ABOUT THIS?

05:36.103 --> 05:37.838
HAPPINESS
IS AN EMPTY BLADDER?

05:37.871 --> 05:40.841
WHAT'S WITH
ALL THE SKIRT FLAPPING?

05:40.874 --> 05:44.311
I WAS DRYING MY...SELF.

05:44.344 --> 05:47.548
SILK CHIFFON.
EXPENSIVE TO DRY‐CLEAN.

05:47.581 --> 05:49.950
CHEWIE TOOK A SHIT
IN A BREAD BAG ONE TIME.

05:49.983 --> 05:51.251
[ LAUGHTER ]

05:51.285 --> 05:55.822
SO, THAT'S WHY I GOT STOPPED?
BECAUSE I PEED?

05:55.856 --> 05:57.090
YEAH, 'CAUSE YOU PEED,

05:57.124 --> 05:58.992
'CAUSE YOU WENT THROUGH
RIGHT AFTER SHIFT CHANGE

05:59.026 --> 06:00.661
WHEN BORDER GUARDS
ARE FRESH AND EAGER,

06:00.694 --> 06:04.131
'CAUSE YOU WORE THAT RIDICULOUS,
CHECK‐MY‐SHIT‐OUT,

06:04.164 --> 06:05.759
TECHNICOLOR SLUT SUIT

06:05.793 --> 06:07.703
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE AFTERNOON
ON A TUESDAY.

06:09.028 --> 06:10.573
WHY YOU CALLING ATTENTION
TO YOURSELF?

06:10.607 --> 06:13.544
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO
BE THE ALL‐AMERICAN MOM.

06:13.577 --> 06:15.212
GET YOURSELF SOME J. CREW.

06:15.246 --> 06:16.547
BLEND, SEÑORA.

06:16.580 --> 06:17.815
BLEND?
YEAH.

06:17.848 --> 06:20.384
LOOK.
LOOK AT YOUR HANDS.

06:20.417 --> 06:21.652
THEY DON'T STOP MOVING.

06:21.685 --> 06:24.522
BANGING ON THE STEERING WHEEL,
TAPPING ON THE DASH,

06:24.555 --> 06:25.589
FANNING YOUR COOCHIE.

06:25.623 --> 06:26.924
I HAD A LOT OF COFFEE.

06:26.957 --> 06:28.692
SO, NEXT TIME,
YOU HAVE LESS.

06:28.726 --> 06:31.896
TAKE SOME BETA BLOCKERS,
OKAY?

06:31.929 --> 06:34.565
JUST CALM YOUR SHIT DOWN.

06:34.598 --> 06:35.566
[ KEY CLICKS ]

06:35.599 --> 06:37.434
WHAT DO YOU NEED
WITH ALL THAT?

06:37.468 --> 06:39.470
THE GUY DIDN'T HAVE
ANY CHANGE.

06:39.503 --> 06:41.672
OH, AND HE WAS
THE ONLY ONE OUT THERE?

06:41.705 --> 06:43.340
LOOK WHAT MESSAGE YOU SENT.

06:43.374 --> 06:46.677
A LADY GOES TO T. J.
DRESSED LIKE A GUERA PEACOCK,

06:46.710 --> 06:49.079
AND SHE COMES BACK
WITH NOTHING BUT THE MIERDA

06:49.113 --> 06:50.915
SHE BUYS IN LINE
AT THE CROSSING.

06:50.948 --> 06:53.450
I TOLD THEM I WAS LOOKING
FOR FADE CREAM.

06:53.484 --> 06:55.019
ALL RIGHT, WELL, WHY DIDN'T
YOU HAVE AND EMPTY CONTAINER

06:55.052 --> 06:57.454
TO SHOW THE GUYS
IN THE STORE, HUH?

06:57.488 --> 06:58.722
WHAT'S THE BRAND NAME?

06:58.756 --> 07:00.925
AH, YOU'RE RIGHT.

07:00.958 --> 07:02.259
I WAS VAGUE.

07:02.293 --> 07:04.495
YOU MUST ALWAYS
BE THINKING AHEAD, OKAY?

07:04.528 --> 07:06.030
KNOW WHAT'S AROUND YOU.

07:06.063 --> 07:07.598
STAY RELAXED.

07:07.631 --> 07:09.099
YOU'VE BEEN THINKING
EAST‐WEST YOUR WHOLE LIFE.

07:09.133 --> 07:10.568
YOU NEED TO START THINKING
NORTH‐SOUTH.

07:10.601 --> 07:13.404
I WANT TO MAKE ANOTHER RUN.

07:13.437 --> 07:14.405
RIGHT NOW.

07:14.438 --> 07:15.739
NAH.
A REAL ONE.

07:15.773 --> 07:18.576
YOU AIN'T READY FOR THAT.

07:18.609 --> 07:20.544
YOU GAVE ME A TEST.
I FAILED.

07:20.578 --> 07:22.346
FINE. BUT I GET IT NOW.

07:22.379 --> 07:25.583
NORTH‐SOUTH. J. CREW.
SMALL BILLS.

07:25.616 --> 07:26.817
BETA BLOCKERS.

07:26.851 --> 07:29.286
SO SCHOOL'S OUT, HMM?

07:29.320 --> 07:30.888
YOU LEARNED ALL YOU NEED?

07:30.921 --> 07:33.290
I LEARNED ALL I'M GONNA LEARN
SITTING IN A WAREHOUSE.

07:33.324 --> 07:36.493
AH, EAGER BEAVER.

07:36.527 --> 07:37.595
Man: OOH!

07:37.628 --> 07:40.064
OKAY, YOU WANT TO MAKE
A REAL RUN?

07:40.097 --> 07:40.931
ALL RIGHT.

07:40.965 --> 07:42.299
THIS TIME
YOU'RE GONNA TAKE MY RIDE.

07:47.137 --> 07:49.473
Andy: UH, THERE ‐‐
THERE'S REALLY ‐‐

07:49.507 --> 07:51.876
THERE'S REALLY NO EASY WAY
TO SAY THIS.

07:51.909 --> 07:54.345
YOU WANT TO KILL BUBBIE.

07:54.378 --> 07:56.180
NO.

07:56.213 --> 07:58.449
WELL, YES, BUT NO.

07:58.482 --> 08:01.352
I MEAN...YES.

08:01.385 --> 08:02.353
AND ALSO NO.

08:02.386 --> 08:03.687
MOSTLY YES.

08:03.721 --> 08:08.492
LIKE AN INCREDIBLY HUMANE,
MERCIFUL, DIGNIFIED "YES,"

08:08.526 --> 08:10.895
UP HERE IN THE FOREGROUND

08:10.928 --> 08:14.231
WITH THIS DEEPLY FELT,
SORROWFUL,

08:14.265 --> 08:19.336
TINGED‐WITH‐REGRET‐AND‐GUILT‐
ABOUT‐THE‐BIG‐FAT‐"YES"

08:19.370 --> 08:22.406
"NO" BACK THERE A WAYS.

08:22.439 --> 08:24.408
I THINK IT'S THE RIGHT THING
TO DO.

08:24.441 --> 08:25.643
OF COURSE YOU DO.

08:25.676 --> 08:26.844
YOU TALK TO DEAD PEOPLE.

08:26.877 --> 08:28.212
IT'S WHAT BUBBIE WANTS.

08:28.245 --> 08:29.580
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

08:29.613 --> 08:32.383
WE DON'T HAVE A WHOLE LOT
OF FAMILY.

08:32.416 --> 08:34.885
DO WE REALLY
WANT TO KILL ONE OFF?

08:34.919 --> 08:38.756
THAT IN THERE, THAT'S AS GOOD
AS IT GETS FOR BUBBIE.

08:38.789 --> 08:40.524
THERE'S NO RECOVERY.

08:40.558 --> 08:43.327
THERE'S JUST PAIN
AND MORE PAIN

08:43.360 --> 08:45.496
AND WANTING THAT PAIN TO END.

08:45.529 --> 08:48.632
SO LET'S JUST KILL HER?

08:48.666 --> 08:50.734
LET'S HELP HER FIND PEACE.

08:50.768 --> 08:53.204
BY KILLING HER.

08:53.237 --> 08:55.639
I WISH YOU WOULDN'T MAKE
"KILLING HER"

08:55.673 --> 08:58.042
SOUND SO MUCH
LIKE "KILLING HER."

08:58.075 --> 09:00.578
SHOW SOME BALLS.

09:00.611 --> 09:01.445
THAT'S THE SPIRIT!

09:01.478 --> 09:02.746
YEAH. SURE.

09:02.780 --> 09:04.815
DEATH IS NO BIG DEAL

09:04.849 --> 09:08.686
BECAUSE LIFE IS JUST...
BLAH BLAH BLAH.

09:08.719 --> 09:12.723
LOOK, SILAS, LIFE IS
JUST BLAH BLAH BLAH.

09:12.756 --> 09:14.458
YOU HOPE FOR BLAH.

09:14.491 --> 09:17.494
AND SOMETIMES YOU FIND IT.

09:17.528 --> 09:20.297
BUT, MOSTLY, IT'S BLAH
AND WAITING FOR BLAH.

09:20.331 --> 09:24.101
AND HOPING YOU WERE RIGHT
ABOUT THE BLAHS YOU MADE.

09:24.134 --> 09:26.237
AND THEN,
JUST WHEN YOU THINK

09:26.270 --> 09:28.939
YOU'VE GOT THE WHOLE
BLAH DAMN THING FIGURED OUT

09:28.973 --> 09:32.743
AND YOU'RE SURROUNDED
BY THE ONES YOU BLAH,

09:32.776 --> 09:35.513
DEATH SHOWS UP.

09:35.546 --> 09:38.782
AND BLAH BLAH BLAH.

09:42.219 --> 09:44.989
ALL RIGHT, LET'S DO THIS.

09:45.022 --> 09:46.423
THAT WAS GOOD.

09:46.457 --> 09:48.559
I HAVE MY MOMENTS.

09:48.592 --> 09:51.629
SO, THE PLAN ‐‐

09:51.662 --> 09:54.265
UNIFIED FRONT,
THREE‐MAN APPROACH.

09:54.298 --> 09:56.901
WE SEND SHANE IN
TO CONVINCE THE OLD MAN.

09:56.934 --> 10:00.271
SILAS AND I HIDE OUT HERE.

10:00.304 --> 10:02.072
WHAT?
HE LIKES YOU.

10:03.140 --> 10:05.576
FINE. PUSSIES.

10:05.609 --> 10:07.411
[ LAUGHS ]

10:10.881 --> 10:12.516
[ LOCK RATTLES, BEEPS ]

10:12.550 --> 10:15.586
FUCKING HOTEL KEY.
SHIT. FUCKER.

10:15.619 --> 10:18.355
MAYBE THEY GAVE YOU
THE WRONG KEY...

10:18.389 --> 10:21.992
FOR YOUR ROOM THAT YOU HAVE
WITH YOUR HUSBAND,

10:22.026 --> 10:24.595
DEAN HODES,
THE LOVABLE GIMP.

10:24.628 --> 10:27.031
YES.

10:27.064 --> 10:28.832
Howser:
<i>LOOK AT THIS THING.</i>

10:28.866 --> 10:30.768
Woman:
<i>DO YOU WANT TO HOLD IT?</i>

10:30.801 --> 10:32.603
NO, I DON'T WANT TO HOLD IT.

10:32.636 --> 10:34.605
<i>BUT WHAT ARE WE</i>
<i>LOOKING AT, EXACTLY?</i>

10:34.638 --> 10:35.739
<i>WHAT IS THIS?</i>

10:35.773 --> 10:37.074
<i>WELL, WHEN THE FIRES</i>
<i>HIT AGRESTIC...</i>

10:37.107 --> 10:39.276
OH, GOD, LOOK.

10:39.310 --> 10:40.244
<i>YOU SAID A "SNEAK"?</i>

10:40.277 --> 10:41.946
<i>YEP, THAT'S THE TERM,</i>
<i>KIND OF LIKE...</i>

10:41.979 --> 10:46.050
OH, I LOVE HUELL HOWSER.
DON'T YOU JUST LOVE HIM, CELIA?

10:46.083 --> 10:48.953
HE'S SO ENTHUSIASTIC.
AND HIS HAIR IS SO NEAT.

10:48.986 --> 10:51.589
PAM, GET YOUR HEAD
OUT OF HUELL'S ASS

10:51.622 --> 10:53.157
AND GO OUT INTO THE HALL.

10:53.190 --> 10:54.358
I NEED A LOOKOUT.

11:00.164 --> 11:04.001
<i>I WASN'T LOOKING AT IT</i>
<i>FROM THE RIGHT ANGLE.</i>

11:04.034 --> 11:05.536
[ SIGHS ]

11:05.569 --> 11:07.505
<i>NOW, SHE KIND OF HAD</i>
<i>A PREMONITION.</i>

11:07.538 --> 11:10.407
"MAIL, MESSAGES...

11:10.441 --> 11:13.210
"SHANE.

11:13.244 --> 11:14.979
"GR8 GRANDMA DYING.

11:15.012 --> 11:16.313
WEIRD HOUSE."

11:16.347 --> 11:18.449
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

11:18.482 --> 11:24.121
"REN MAR IS FULL
OF BEACH NAZIS."

11:24.154 --> 11:27.558
REN MAR.

11:27.591 --> 11:29.260
REN MAR.

11:32.496 --> 11:33.497
¿SABE?

11:33.531 --> 11:35.499
REGRESE COMO UNA HORA
O DOS HORAS.

11:35.533 --> 11:39.303
NO, UM...
SORRY, NO COMPRENDE.

11:39.336 --> 11:41.005
FARMACIA.

11:41.038 --> 11:42.273
OH, NO.

11:42.306 --> 11:46.277
NO, I'M GONNA STAY HERE
AND WATCH AND LISTEN. SEE?

11:49.880 --> 11:51.382
YA.

11:51.415 --> 11:53.984
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

11:54.018 --> 11:55.519
YO ENTIENDO ACÁ.
OKAY, PUES.

11:55.553 --> 11:57.021
¿QUé CREES?

11:57.054 --> 11:58.789
Woman:
[ <i>Spanish accent</i> ] <i>HELLO,</i>

11:58.822 --> 12:01.392
<i>WELCOME TO PODCAST</i>
<i>NUMBER SIX ‐‐ "SHOPPING."</i>

12:01.425 --> 12:06.197
<i>HOLA, BIENVENIDOS A PODCAST</i>
<i>NúMERO SEIS, "COMPRAR."</i>

12:06.230 --> 12:09.133
<i>NOW THAT YOU HAVE PURCHASED</i>
<i>NEW SHOES,</i>

12:09.166 --> 12:12.236
<i>LET'S GO NEXT DOOR</i>
<i>TO THE PET STORE ‐‐</i>

12:12.269 --> 12:14.271
<i>LA TIENDA DE MASCOTAS.</i>

12:14.305 --> 12:16.307
<i>DO YOU HAVE VIDEO FOR CATS?</i>

